function sortNamesByHeight(names, heights) {
    let nameHeightPairs = [];

    for(let i = 0; i < names.length; i++) {
        nameHeightPairs.push({name: names[i], height: heights[i]});
    }

    nameHeightPairs.sort((a, b) => b.height - a.height);

    let sortedNames = nameHeightPairs.map(pair => pair.name);

    return sortedNames;
}
```

    The algorithm starts by iterating through both input arrays (`names` and `heights`) to create an array ('name_height_pairs') of pairs (in other languages, objects with `height` and `name` properties) containing the heights and corresponding names.

Next, the array of pairs is sorted in descending order (highest to lowest) based on the height values.

Finally, a new array (`sorted_names`) is created containing only the names from the sorted pairs.

This process ensures that the names in the final array are sorted in descending order by the people's heights.

